name: Field Top Bar & Restaurant

reviews.review_text: Staff was nice but the food and the atmosphere were bad. The dosa was expired and the sambar tasted like leftover fish curry and the hand wash didn’t have light and it was very stinky. The only good thing is that they remained calm and they did not charge us.

My recent visit to this restaurant was a seriously disappointing and frankly,upsetting experience.intending to order from the menu which featured standard items like biryani and fried rice.The serving person told us to try the fish curry. We were, however, immediately presented with three plates of fish curry and white rice, a dish which, notably, was not listed on the menu at all.When the bill arrived, we were shocked to find that the total cost of the fish curry was 3 plates (7500), while the white rice was (1260).When I brought this to the attention of the management, they justified the exorbitant prices by saying that similar restaurants in Goa charge similarly. However, a quick visit to another restaurant the next day revealed that I could get a similar dish - fish curry with rice and fish fry - for a mere 180  This stark contrast in pricing only added to my disappointment and frustration.

We had a very disappointing experience at Field Top Bar and Restaurant. The attitude of the staff was extremely careless, and the service was appalling. It took around 20 minutes to get our food, which was just vada, chai, and dosa. If they had informed us upfront that it would take time, we would have been fine with it. Instead, they assured us it would be delivered quickly, which is why we placed the order. Even worse, we didn’t get our chai until we stood up to leave out of frustration. When it finally arrived, it was the worst tea we’ve ever had—more like sugar mixed with tea powder.

We also ordered a ghee roast, and to our shock, the ghee was spoiled, making it taste terrible. The washroom area was filthy, which added to the unpleasant experience.

To top it all off, the prices were exorbitant. For just 4 vadas, 1 ghee roast, 2 teas, and 2 coffees, the bill was over ₹500. Had the food been good, we wouldn’t have minded the cost, but with such poor quality and service, it felt like a complete waste of money.

Definitely not a place we’d recommend or return to.

description:
### A Dive into Field Top Bar & Restaurant: An Arpora Experience

Nestled in the vibrant tourist hub of Arpora, Field Top Bar & Restaurant presents itself as a casual dining destination beckoning food lovers with a rating of 3.4 based on 1,672 reviews. Notable tags such as **Goan** (18 mentions), **fish curry** (13 mentions), and **fish fry** (6 mentions) hint at a culinary journey steeped in local flavor and tradition. However, a closer inspection of customer feedback reveals a contrasting narrative that may leave potential diners cautious.

#### Ambiance & Design

Upon entering Field Top, guests are greeted by a blend of casual dining aesthetics reminiscent of a typical Goan eatery, with basic décor aimed at comfort rather than elegance. While specific lighting details were scarce in the reviews, photos reveal an unpretentious setting that emphasizes functionality. Tables appear simple, and the atmosphere seems geared towards quick, casual dining rather than a leisurely experience. However, this informal vibe can sometimes lend itself to a chaotic dining experience, particularly when the restaurant is busy.

#### Menu & Culinary Experience

The menu at Field Top is rather standard for the region, featuring traditional items such as biryani and fried rice alongside local specialties like **fish curry**. While customers initially intended to sample these menu staples, recurring feedback suggests a disconnect between what is offered and what appears on the menu. For instance, several patrons were surprised to receive plates of fish curry that were not listed, resulting in shockingly high bills. One customer detailed an experience where three plates of fish curry amounted to ₹7,500—in stark contrast to better prices found elsewhere.

Unfortunately, the culinary execution did not meet expectations; reports of expired dosa and subpar tea were not uncommon. The presentation of dishes also failed to impress, as described by customers who were let down by quality and service alike. The dissatisfaction extended to ambient hygiene, with reviews noting a lack of cleanliness in the washroom area.

#### Customer Experience & Service

Service at Field Top has been described as inconsistent and, at times, neglectful. Several patrons expressed frustration with long wait times for food, poor communication regarding delays, and a general lack of attentiveness from the staff. One review poignantly noted that despite orders taken for quick items, it took an agonizing 20 minutes to receive the food, and after the wait, the dish was far from satisfactory. Comments on excessive pricing, especially relative to the quality received, further compounded negative sentiments. It appeared that while the staff attempted to maintain calm in challenging situations, fundamental issues regarding service efficiency and food quality remained unaddressed.

#### Popularity & Reviews

Despite a significant number of reviews, feedback overall leans towards the disappointing side—multiple reviews highlighted alarming issues with both food and service. While some visitors may come for the **tourist-friendly** atmosphere, the lack of reliable dining experiences tends to overshadow any goodwill. Those following online chatter should be wary, as social media and review sites echo similar narratives of dissatisfaction.

#### Utilizing Visual Content

Photos shared by customers reveal the simple—yet flawed—presentation of their meals, showcasing plates where food quality appears to be less than desirable. The lack of engaging visuals often contributes to the impression of neglect within both food preparation and the dining environment. Visuals of the restaurant's interior do not convey a welcoming ambiance, with a hint of disorganization evident.

### Conclusion

In summary, while Field Top Bar & Restaurant aims to entice diners with Goan flavors and a casual dining atmosphere, it grapples with significant operational hurdles. Consequently, diners seeking quality culinary experiences may find better options in the surrounding area. With an attentive eye to customer feedback and a commitment to improved standards, there may yet be hope for this establishment to rise above the current sentiment. For those seeking to explore Goan cuisine, it might be prudent to tread carefully—or look elsewhere altogether.
